  "2026-07-19T04:07:48.361Z",maintainer-agent,"Family-map addition 2026-07-19: NEW artifact class - SDK workspace-transaction journals (<pmRoot>/transactions/sdk/<txid>.json, shipped PR#605). Per-branch runtime receipts that conflict on every concurrent merge if the repo tracks .agents/pm; not covered by the init gitignore block and never GC'd. Owned by new pm-8xod (parent usfg, related here) - gitignore-block coverage + retention/GC + tracked-repo merge disposition. No change to the execution order gates (cxyv, ol3p first)."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T03:44:41.187Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-19 intake wave. Maintainer dogfood issues GH-595..612 landed a verified multi-agent branch-merge defect matrix; the artifact-class children now under this feature: pm-wc1r (GH-599 history jsonl driver, Feature P1), pm-9q2t (GH-606 .toon count-header appends, P1), pm-m3nl (GH-608 updated_at scalar conflicts), pm-wwfd (GH-611 delete/modify resurrection, P1), pm-xdn6 (GH-609 config/schema layer), pm-gpo7 (GH-603 history-repair cements loss, P1), pm-ol3p (GH-604 verify strict-exit gate). Outside this parent but in the family: pm-cxyv (GH-607 validate skips unparseable items, under pm-33cw), pm-pibw (GH-600 cross-branch id collisions, under pm-dj98), pm-4uqm (GH-598 gitignore hardcoded root), pm-xh82 (GH-612 additive AC). Suggested execution order: cxyv+ol3p (gates first — make corruption visible), then wc1r+9q2t+m3nl (drivers), then wwfd+xdn6 (policies), gpo7 rides the wc1r+ol3p loop. GH-610 closed as dup of GH-590 (shipped PR#593)."
  "2026-07-19T11:17:45.254Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-19 reconciliation (post-PR#614): the entire first merge-safety wave SHIPPED — all seven children closed (wc1r history JSONL union/reanchor driver, 9q2t field-aware .toon item driver, m3nl updated_at latest-timestamp resolution, xdn6 JSON config/schema key-level driver, cxyv validate --check-storage-integrity, ol3p history --verify --strict-exit, gpo7 cross-author reconciliation reports in repair) plus 4uqm custom-root gitignore and 8xod transactions GC (gc --scope transactions). GH-598/599/603/604/606/607/608/609/611 all closed. Execution order held: gates → drivers → policies. Public SDK primitives: field-aware item merge, history union/reanchor, recursive JSON merge; installer via `pm merge install` (idempotent fenced .gitattributes + local driver config, real %P paths). Docs: MERGE_SAFETY.md.\n\nRemaining frontier under this umbrella: pm-iwsj (adopt the drivers + CI integrity/verify gates in the pm-cli repo itself — migration steps from PR#614 are NOT yet applied here: no .gitattributes fence, no CI storage-integrity/strict-exit step), pm-pibw (cross-branch id collisions, parent dj98), and any policy-layer work (merge policy selection per artifact class) stays extend-here, never new umbrellas."
body: "## Context\nGit-native storage is a hard constraint (ADR pm-i7i4: the filesystem is the database; ADR pm-bl8x decision driver: everything must remain \"diffable, mergeable, and recoverable from the working tree alone\"). But pm has never defined what \"mergeable\" actually means when two branches mutate the same item: worktree agents branch from main today, and at thousands of concurrent agents, branch-and-merge becomes a primary workflow, not an edge case.\n\n## Problem\n- Two branches editing the same `.toon` item file produce raw git conflicts with no field-aware resolution guidance (last-writer-wins on a whole file loses the other branch's fields).\n- History JSONL streams are hash-chained (appendLineAtomic anchoring): a naive union merge of two diverged `history/<id>.jsonl` files breaks chain integrity; `pm history-repair` (shipped in pm-85hm) can re-anchor drift but is not merge-aware and must be invoked manually per item.\n- There is no post-merge verification story: `pm validate` / `pm health` do not flag \"this workspace was just merged and N history chains diverged / M items have conflict markers\".\n\n## Deliverables (scope for grooming)\n1. Documented merge semantics per artifact class: item `.toon` (field-level three-way guidance or documented ours/theirs policy), history `.jsonl` (union + mandatory re-anchor), locks/runtime (ignore), search index (rebuild).\n2. `.gitattributes` recommendations and, if justified, a custom git merge driver shipped as a pm package (check existing unbraind packages first — none cover this as of 2026-07-07 review #16).\n3. Post-merge reconciliation entrypoint: e.g. `pm validate --post-merge` advisory or doctor check that detects conflict markers, diverged chains, and duplicate IDs from parallel branch creation (relates to pm-khdq ID TOCTOU), with remediation hints wiring into history-repair.\n4. Docs: worktree/branch agent workflow guidance (AGENT_GUIDE) covering when to branch tracker data vs. mutate main.\n\n## Relationships\n- pm-is1a (multi-workspace federation) is the superset problem; single-workspace multi-branch merge is the prerequisite and should land first.\n- SDK-first (pm-usfg): reconciliation logic lands as an SDK primitive; CLI is a shim.\n- Horizon: long (with pm-9rxu scale-out); design/ADR input can start earlier.\n\n## Duplicate check (2026-07-07 review #16)\nSearched \"merge conflict branch tracker\", \"merge driver git worktree branches\", \"post-merge reconcile history chain\" — only history-repair (pm-85hm, shipped, drift-only) and consolidation item pm-tqel matched; no existing item covers merge semantics or post-merge reconciliation."
